A policeman simply identified as Sergeant Bello has shot and murdered at least six of his colleagues in Maiduguri, Borno State. It was gathered that the incident happened recently in the police college quarters of Borno Police headquarters in Maiduguri The police sergeant reportedly had a misunderstanding with his wife, prompting neighbors to intervene. However, he was opposed to neighbors’ intervention. US Top Diplomat Meets With NATO Chief On Russia-Ukraine Crisis APC Crisis Deepens As Buhari’s Imposition Of Adamu, Others Tears… The wife was said to have left her matrimonial home due to maltreatment. “He started shooting and threatened to kill everyone. Unfortunately, he shot people, but six mobile policemen died and two others are currently receiving treatment at Specialist Hospital,” a source said. The officer was also reported to have razed down two blocks of eight rooms in the process, while also shooting his father-in-law.